Goal: {{ goal }}

## Output instructions

Return your result using the structured `PlanningAgentResult` schema. Do NOT write files, create documents, or use terminal commands. Your entire deliverable is expressed through the structured output fields:

- `tickets` — a list of `PlanningTicket` objects, one per implementation ticket. Each ticket has:
  - `ticketId` — short unique identifier (e.g. `TICKET-001`)
  - `title` — one-line title
  - `description` — what must be implemented and why
  - `tasks` — list of `TicketTask` (taskId, description, estimatedHours, relatedFiles)
  - `dependencies` — list of ticketIds this ticket depends on
  - `acceptanceCriteria` — list of testable acceptance conditions
  - `effortEstimate` — e.g. `"small"`, `"medium"`, `"large"`
  - `priority` — integer priority (1 = highest)
- `output` — a human-readable summary of the plan and any rationale

Do not write the plan to any file path. Do not use Edit, Write, or Terminal tools. Return the structured result directly.

